The paper deals with the problem of identifying time-varying linear systems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of signal processing. The paper specifically focuses on the identification of underspread linear systems, which is a subfield of signal processing that deals with signals whose energy is concentrated in a small region of the time-frequency plane. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and computational techniques to solve the identification problem, which suggests that it may also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the results to radar, which suggests that it may also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
